  "prompt": "Are the jobs that president-elect Donald Trump saved in Indiana at the carrier plant Union or non-union?",
  "response": "The jobs that President-elect Donald Trump saved at the Carrier plant in Indiana were primarily union jobs. Carrier, a subsidiary of United Technologies Corporation, announced in 2016 that it would keep approximately 800 jobs at its Indianapolis plant in the United States after negotiations with the incoming Trump administration. Many of these jobs were represented by the United Steelworkers Union, which had been active in advocating for the workers at the plant. The deal to save these jobs was part of a broader effort by the Trump administration to retain manufacturing jobs in the U.S., though it was met with mixed reactions and some criticism regarding the long-term sustainability and the number of jobs actually saved.",
